items.content:

As per the inside reports,
Boyapati Seenu, who gave back-t-back hits Simha and Legend to Bala Krishna will helm his 100th movie, while Sai Korrapati is likely to produce the movie on a lavish scale on huge budget under Varahi Chalana Chitra banner.

The storyline discussions seem to have already commenced, and we hear Bala Krishna’s 100th film will be titled God Father. Well, the powerful title seems to be apt for Bala Krishna as his fans immensely like it. The cast and crew finalization and other script discussions are being carried, and an official announcement of Bala Krishna’s 100th film will be made post Sankranthi 2016.

The film shot in bilingual versions casting Simbu in Tamil and Naga Chaitanya in Telugu languages is scheduled for December end release in both versions. However, the official release date announcement is awaited.

Gautham Vasudev Menon wielded the megaphone

The shooting schedules of Sahasam Swasaga Saagipo have been wrapped up, and the post-production works are under progress. Ravinder Reddy is producing the movie, while Ace writer Kona Venkat acts as Presenter. Sahasam Swasaga Saagipo has musical scores by Maestro AR Rahman.

Sahasam Swasaga Saagipo, from the makers of Ye Maya Chesave is riding high with expectations. Can Naga Chaitanya, Gautham Menon and AR Rahman repeat the YMC magic?

items.title: Experimental Movies in Tollywood sets cash registers ringing !
items.content:
Tollywood welcomes Unique Content-based big-budget Movies


While Tollywood makers are opting for fresh and unique concepts, Telugu cinema lovers are welcoming the unconventional and experimentation. Experiments in Tollywood
is not new, as several medium-budget producers have always tried to come out with unique concepts, but the years 2014-2015 are a bit different, as event the big producers are in a mood to experiment and spending whopping amounts, showing confidence on Star actors and filmmakers.

To start off, Akkineni family’s Manam, Venkatesh’s Drishyam are a couple of super hit experiments released previous year, and audiences loved the content and uniqueness. 1-Nenokkadine is one of the high-budgeted experiments in Tollywood, but the film resulted as a commercial failure due to its whopping investment, though Mahesh Babu’s performance has received loads of applauds from A centers.

However, the year 2015 seems to be the year of experiments with Allu Arjun's S/O Satyamurthy, Pawan Kalyan, Venkatesh starrer Gopala Gopala garnering decent collections besides earning good applauds.

Then came S.S. Rajamouli's magnum opus Baahubali - The Beginning which has taken trade pundits by surprise with its massive collections, by entering Rs.200 crore club worldwide in just 5 days of run. Baahubali has taken the Telugu cinema to the next level, and it turned out to be a stupendous hit not just in Telugu, but also in other versions of Tamil, Malayalam and Hindi too. . Irrespective of the language, 'Baahubali' has entertained audiences worldwide, which itself is the biggest accomplishment for the makers. The 250 Crore film is about two brothers at war for the rule of ancient kingdom.

Mahesh Babu’s Srimanthudu is yet another big-budget film that has set the cash registers ringing at the Box-Office. The film has a strong story, and Mahesh’s characterizations are very much different from his regular roles in commercial entertainers. His role as Harsha is reserved yet emotionally strong and has got good response, and Mahesh has given full credit to director Koratala Siva for handling his character and film striking chords with audiences.


Director Krish is one filmmaker who always pushes the envelope content-wise, and he has a niche fan base. His films are not commercial hits, but Kanche proved otherwise and is managing to garner decent collections at the box-office. Casting Varun Tej, Pragya in leads, Kanche film was released with English subtitles, it opened to overwhelming response. The war-based period movie is set against the World War II backdrop and the unit has shot war scenes in Georgia. The dialogues and the racy screenplay were major assets.

Nani’s recent release Bhale Bhale Magadivoy has turned out to be a bumper hit, that the film has even managed to cross has grossed 10 crore in its opening weekend, and the makers have made good profits with the medium-budget entertainer at the end of the full run for this 6 cr budget flick. Director Maruthi has made the film in quite entertaining format that is liked equally by family audiences and youth alike.


It is also the season in proving the women-power in Telugu film industry. Heroines are looking for changes in this hero-dominant industry grabbing the woman-centric films. Arundhati actress Anushka Shetty is always ready for powerful female-centric characters and as many as three of her powerful-role films reached screens in 2015. She had a small-but powerful role in Baahubali first part, while Anushka has delivered brilliant performance as Queen Rudrama Devi in Gunasekhar’s directorial. The film had a decent successful run at the box-office, and resulted as average grosser due to high budget constraints.

Anushka Shetty’s Size Zero by director Prakash Kovelamudi is one of the much-awaited experimental flicks, where the makers comes with a message that “Beauty is skin deep and it’s about accepting yourself the way you are.” Anushka has taken a bold decision of putting on 20 kgs to suit the part in the film, which also features Arya and Sonal Chauhan as other leads. The teaser trailers of Size Zero have got excellent response and Tollywood fans are eagerly waiting for the movie release.

Nagarjuna, Karthi and Tamanna are teaming up for an offbeat film Oopiri, a Tamil-Telugu bilingual in Vamsi Paidipally direction. Oopiri is the official remake French comedy-drama The Intouchables, but the makers have implemented changes for Telugu, Tamil nativity. Oopiri is all about a bond that links the relationship between two mates and symbolizes friendship. Santosh Narayanan is composing feel good songs and PVP Cinemas is the production house.


With the most big-budget Experimental films setting the cash registers ringing at the Box-Office, can we expect few more Tollywood Star actors and directors coming up with unique and fresh storylines, leaving aside the regular and routine commercial entertainers? Well, let’s hope so…

Rao Ramesh, Satyam Rajesh, Shakalaka Shankar, Sanjay Mishra, Pitubash Tripati are playing supporting roles in the film. Praveen Lakkaraju is the music composer while cinematography is by Sai Sreeram. Uday Nandanavanam is the director and MVV Satyanarayana is producing Sankarabharanam which is releasing on Decembr 4th.

With Anushka, Arya and Sonal Chuhan in the lead roles, Size Zero directed by K Raghavendra’s son K S Prakash is gearing up for a grand release on 27th November. The unique content and trailers are raising curiosity on the movie, and the trailer has already earned 2 million views.

Anushka is playing the main lead
in this woman-centric film, but there are lots of guest appearances from the star appearances to look out for. Star actors including Nagarjuna, Rana, Lakshmi Manchu, Jeeva, Kajal Agarwal, Tamannah, Hansika, Sri Divya and Revathy have done cameo roles in the film, in support of the movie. items.title: Soggade Chinni Nayana joins Pongal race
items.content:
Nagarjuna’s Soggade Chinni Nayana has joined the Pongal race, as the producers are contemplating to release the film on January 15th, 2016. Earlier the makers announced that Soggade Chinni Nayana will release in December, but with the delay in the post-production works, the makers have planned to postpone it for Pongal.

Soggade Chinni Nayana casts
Nagarjuna in dual roles as grandfather and grandson pairing up with Ramya Krishna and Lavanya Tripati. The film’s story is laced with socio-fantasy elements.

Kalyan Krishna is making his directorial debut with Soggade Chinni Nayana, and Nagarjuna, Ram Mohan P are the producers. Made on Annapurna Studios and Sunshine Cinemas Pvt Ltd banners, Soggade Chinni Nayana has PS Vinod’s camera work and Anup Rubens tunes.

An official announcement on Soggade Chinni Nayana release date will be made soon, along with the new trailer launch.

The shoot is being canned in the rustic locales of Rajamundry.

Titled Sarainodu, Boyapati Srinu

Anjali is roped in for a special song in the movie and Srikanth, Pradeep Rawat are playing key roles.

Allu Arvind is producing the film on Geetha Arts banner with SS Thaman as music composer and Rishi Punjabi as cinematographer.

items.content:
Venkatesh and Maruthi were supposed to act in Radha film earlier, but the film was shelved after the movie was launched, as a writer claimed that Radha story was his own and not director Maruthi’s.

The duo however has sorted the
issues, and is finally set to team up again for a new project, and the Radhakrishna is the title under discussion for the film. After Lakshmi and Tulasi films, Venkatesh and Nayanatara are set to team up again for this new movie.

items.content:

The current schedule shoot is being canned in Ramoji Film City, where the unit is filming some crucial scenes on principal cast including Mahesh Babu and Satyaraj.

The unit was supposed to begin
Ooty schedule in November, but it was postponed by a month. The schedule will now commence on December 8, and scenes featuring lead cast and a couple of songs will be filmed.

Casting Samantha, Kajal Aggarwal, Pranitha as leading ladies, Brahmotsavam is a family entertainer being directed by Srikanth Addala in Telugu-Tamil bilingual versions. This PVP Cinema production house movie has Mickey J Meyer’s compositions.

Palnati Surya Prathap donned the director cap for Kumari 21F, while Sukumar produced the film, besides penning the story and screenplay. Top Class technicians Ratnavelu and Devi Sri Prasad handled the cinematography and soundtrack for Kumari 21F.

items.title: Tollywood Actresses and their Businesses Ventures
items.content:
Tollywood celebrities especially the heroines are facing the reality in Cinema industry, and are creating better sources of outcome by investing in other business or making their hobbies into a business, so that any ebb and flow in movies will not affect them financially.

Delhi beauty Taapsee Pannu
besides being busy with Tamil, Telugu and Hindi films has started her own business, a wedding planning company, Wedding Factory. Tapsee joined with her sister Shaguna and her friend Farah Parvaresh for managing the business. The actress has informed that they have already launched a website to promote the business.

Nisha Agarwal who has bid adieu to films after her wedding was involved in jewellery brand business called Marsala. Nisha says, “Actresses have shelf life and they can’t be acting all their lives. Marsala is a sustainable business model, I’m happy to start such jewellery brand, as it was perfect thing for me.”

Actress Sanjjanaa, besides acting in Telugu, Kannada, Tamil films has also turned co-producer and invested in several Kannada films. She has also started the Akshar Power Yoga Academy, a premium power yoga lounge in Bengaluru, which is the 9th centre in the city.

Punjabi beauty Charmme Kaur, who made her Tollywood entry long back, has started her own production house CK Entertainments and produced Jyothi Lakshmi. She is also in plans to produce other stars films and is pretty confident on her production knowledge, besides confident of her team. “There’s no money that goes in or out without my knowledge. I have a fantastic team, that helps a lot,” she adds.

Lakshmi Manchu who is an actor-producer and also a show hostess has launched a perfume in her name under the brand Iconoplast. She unveiled the exclusive fragrance recently in Hyderabad. The multifaceted actress s also planning to launch a luxury expo under Iconoplast brand name joining the lineup of actors like Amitabh Bachchan, Shah Rukh Khan, Shilpa Shetty, Arjun Ram Pal and Lata Mangeshkar who launch their own fragrances.

Goan beauty Ileana has recently brought in a fashion cloth store, but also a boutique under the name ILIEANA.  The cloth store is in INORBIT mall at Hyderabad, and the Ileana has plans to extend it to U.S, Mumbai and other parts of places.

Milky Beauty Tamanna has turned entrepreneur launching her own Gold designer jerwellery store “White and Gold” The store not only is restricted to her own designs but also has her favourite collections of Gold designs for sale.

There are several other actresses who are investing in other businesses like Namitha investing in Real Estate ventures, Bipasha Basu launching her fashion brand apparel, Trisha planning for a Hotel business at al.

So, the talented actresses are not only shining in the films, but also in their Business by looking for other sources of income financially. Well, we call them Beauties with Brains…

Experimental Movies in Tollywood sets cash registers ringing !

items.title: Akhil Telugu Movie Review
items.content:
Akkineni clan Akhil Akkineni hero debut film Akhil has been released today in good number of screens with loads of expectations. Sayeesha Saighal is the lead actress while VV Vinayak is the director and Thaman and Anup Rubens are the music composers of the film. Nithin is the producer of this commercial action entertainer. 

Story :- 

Akhil (Akkineni Akhil) is a street smart guy who loves Divya (Sayeesha Siagal) and to impress her he goes to Spain with her. In the admist Akhil involves in a tussle between the Russian czar and African tribals who are safeguarding Jua (A Metal Object which is meant for saving the world from years).  Rest of the story is how Akhil plays his smart play with the villains and give his helping hand to tribals forms crux of the story ?

Performances :- 

Akhil made a positive debut with this film and shows he has long time to run. He is good at action scenes and dances are awesome on the big screens. He should get better in his Expressions.

Sayeesha Saighal has on-screen chemistry with Akhil and does a clean performance in his debutante act in Tollywood. Sayeesha is trained dancer and she proves with ease in the dances. She is gorgeous in songs.

Brahmanandam is hilarious, Vennela Kishore is good, Mahesh Manjrekar is impressive and Rajendra Prasad is ok. Sapthagiri does his part to his part and others are adequate.

Technical Analysis :-

Thaman SS and Anup Rubens tunes are just ok while Mani Sharma gets the whole credit as his Background score elevated most of the scenes. Cinematography by Amol Rathod is neat and dialogues are apt. The VFX and other Graphical works are very bad to mention. VV Vinayak couldn't handle the good story with pale screenplay and weak narration. Production values are standard.

Analysis:-

First half of Akhil begins with impressive note of fight and song and from then the narration is racy which on-go reveals the main plot of the story. With few entertaining elements this has couple of songs which are well executed. Akhil Akkineni is filled with energy in dances and in action scenes. Pre-Climax sequences leaves curiosity for the later half.

Second half begins with the concept but without a logic in sequences. The story which goes to Africa looses its novelty of International backdrop of the aim saving the world. Main drawback in this half is VFX episodes and comedy with is routine and narration is weak but it is dragged. Climax scenes totally lacks the logic and final plane fight looks silly. 

ZC Take :- 

Akhil Akkineni does a cool debut but Akhil misses the Goal of a Hero... 

Zustcinema Akhil Rating :- 2.75 / 5

items.title: Nani’s film completes pre-release business without title!
items.content:
Nani has always proved his mettle with acting skills, and he is on cloud nine with the success of Maruthi directorial Bhale Bhale Magadivoy, which showed its affect on his next film too.

Nani has signed up for yet another
romantic-comedy entertainer in the direction of Hanu Raghavapudi of Andhala Rakshasi film, and we hear that the film has already completed its pre-release business, without even the makers announcing the title of the project. Reportedly, the entire pre-release business of the movie has been wrapped up.

The shooting schedules of the film are progressing at a brisk pace, and the makers will announce the release details soon.

Anil Sunkara, Ram Achanta and Gopichand Achanta are producing the yet-to-be titled film on 14 Reels Entertainment banner with Yuvaraj as director of photography, Vishal as music director, Avinash as art director and MR Varma as editor.

items.title: Allu Arjun in Manam fame Vikram Kumar direction?
items.content:
Stylish Star Allu Arjun juggles between mass action-dramas as well as romantic comedy entertainers, and thus he has a good fan base among all sections of mass, youth and family audiences.

Allu Arjun who is currently acting in a
commercial mass entertainer Sarainodu with Boyapati Srinu, is now set to team up with director Vikram Kumar of Manam fame for a family entertainer. Allu Arjun was impressed with Vikram Kumar’s Manam apparently, and the Stylish Star is keen to act in his direction soon.

However, it will take some time for Allu Arjun, Vikram Kumar combo to hit the floors, as the duo has been busy with their respective films Sarainodu and Suriya starrer 24.

We also hear Allu Arjun has been replaced by Naga Chaitanya in Gautham Menon’s multi-lingual flick planned to be made in Telugu, Tamil, Kannada and Malyalam versions. Stay tuned to this space for official confirmation.

items.title: Gopichand, Regina’s Soukyam release on December 25
items.content:
Gopichand is currently acting in the direction of AS Ravi Kumar Chowdary for a new film Soukyam, and the makers are planning to release the movie on 25th of December on the eve of Christmas.

Regina Cassandra is roped in as the
leading lady in the movie. Ravikumar Chowdary has directed Gopichand for super hit film Yagnam and Regina in yet another hit Pilla Nuvvu Leni Jeevitham. Soukyam however marks the first combo of Gopichand and Regina. The first look of the film is awaited soon.

Soukyam touted to be a family entertainer laced with emotional drama, is being produced by V.Anand Prasad on Bhavya Creations banner with story and dialogues by Gopi Mohan and Kona Venkat. Prasad Murella is the DOP and Anup Rubens is providing tunes.

Shavukaru Janaki, Raghubabu, Jayaprakash Reddy, Prudhvi, Nassar, Mukesh Rushi, Pradeep Rawat are laying key roles in the film.

The unit members have already canned a

Srikanth Addala is directing Mahesh Babu for the second time after the successful Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu. The film casts three lead ladies Samantha, Kajal Agarwal and Pranitha.

items.title: Soggade Chinni Nayana trailers with Akhil
items.content:
It’s a double delight for all Akkineni fans this Diwali. While the fans are eagerly waiting to watch the Akkineni clan Akhil in his debut movie releasing on November 11, their excitement further goes up with  Nagarjuna’s upcoming film Soggade Chinni Nayana (SCN) theatrical trailer to be attached to Akhil screens.

Soggade Chinni Nayana teaser trailer got
very good response, and the theatrical trailer will be played in Akhil screening. The shoot of Soggade Chinni Nayana has almost been wrapped up, and the makers are planning to release it in December, though an official announcement is awaited.

New comer Kalyan Krishna wielded the megaphone for Soggade Chinni Nayana, where Nagarjuna plays dual roles in the film and Ramya Krishna, Lavanya Tripathi as his heroines. With Anasuya and Hamasa Nandini in key roles, the film produced jointly by Radha Mohan P and Nagarjuna has music by Anup Rubens.

items.content:
Young Tiger NTR’s Nannaku Prematho unit is wrapping up the Hyderabad schedule shoot and the unit will soon head to Spain for an extensive schedule shoot, with which the entire shoot gets almost completed.

With significant portions of the
Nannaku Prematho shoot already getting wrapped, the team has begun the post production works in parallel. Sources are a buzz that the editing and DI work for the first half is already been completed, and the unit members are happy with the result. The other post-production works are in the advanced stage.

Stylish filmmaker Sukumar is wielding the megaphone for Nannaku Prematho, and the teaser trailer has got terrific response. NTR will be seen in never-before-seen stylish look while Rakul Preet Singh plays his love interest.

Produced by BVSN Prasad on SVCC banner, Nannaku Prematho has music by Devi Sri Prasad.

items.title: Size Zero Trailer counts 1 Million Views
items.content:
Trailer of PVP Cinema’s “Size Zero” reaches over 1 million views on Youtube.

“Size Zero”, PVP Cinema’s upcoming film,
is directed by K. S. Prakash Rao and stars Anushka Shetty, Arya and Sonal Chauhan in the lead roles. A bilingual project, the film is also being released in Tamil as “Inji Iduppazhagi”

The audio of the film, composed by the legendary M. M. Keeravani, was launched along with the trailer on Nov. 1 in a grand, star-studded event at Novotel HICC. The success of the event is now being mimicked by the audio and trailer of the film.

In just a few days, the trailers of both, “Size Zero” and “Inji Iduppazhagi”, have scored over 1 million views each while the audio has received an overwhelming positive response from audiences.

With Anushka’s birthday tomorrow, such good news could not have come at a better time.

Both films, “Size Zero” and “Inji Iduppazhagi”, are scheduled to release on Nov. 27.

items.title: Pawan Kalyan’s Sardaar Gabbar Singh release date
items.content:
Power Star Pawan Kalyan’s much awaited Sardaar Gabbar Singh is likely to hit the big-screens on April 8 as summer treat. An official confirmation will be made by the makers of the movie sometime soon.

The schedule shoot is presently
taking place in and around Hyderabad, and the unit will soon be heading to Gujarat on the 17th of this month for a long schedule, where major key portions will be canned. Kajal Agarwal, who is roped in as the lead actress will be joining the sets from the next schedule in Gujarat. Ali and Brahmaji are partaking in the Hyderabad schedule.

KS Ravindra of Power fame is directing Sardaar Gabbar Singh, while the basic storyline is penned by Pawan Kalyan, who has also given his inputs for the screenplay along with the other team.

Produced by Sharrath Marar on North Star Entertainments in association with Eros International, this Gabbar Singh sequel has Devi Sri Prasad’s music.

items.title: Bala Krishna’s Dictator shoot wrap in a week
items.content:
Bala Krishna's upcoming film Dictator has reached the final leg of the shoot, and the film is just a week away from its completion. A fight sequence is being filmed currently at a pub in Hyderabad city and it will be wrapped up, while the unit will be canning the rest of the shoot next week in Delhi schedule.

With this schedule, the entire
shoot gets wrapped up and the makers have already filmed the songs in abroad, in the earlier schedules. The post-production works will commence soon, and Dictator is being planned for January 14th, 2016, Pongal release.

Dictator audio scores composed by SS Thaman will be launched on December 20, on a grand scale in Amaravati. Casting Anjali and Sonal Chauhan as the leading ladies, Dictator is directed by Sriwass of Loukyam fame and has screenplay and dialogues by Gopimohan and Kona Venkat.

Bala Krishna will be seen in two different shades in Dictator, and the film is riding on huge expectations with a good pre-release business.

items.title: Rajinikanth’s Kabali look get terrific response
items.content:
Superstar Rajinikanth is referred as style icon of Indian Cinema, and his histrionics and style are admired by millions of audiences. Rajinikanth seem to be redefining his style at the age of 64, in his forthcoming film Kabali, as his look in the posters are getting terrific response.

Kabali first photoshoot has been released long back, and the makers have recently released location pictures of Rajinikanth from the film, which has gone viral in the web media delighting all the Thalaiva fans. With the white beard, classy goggles and blazers, Rajinikanth is sure rocking the stills and raising the curiosity on Kabali.

The shooting schedules of Kabali are progressing at a brisk pace in Malaysia, and the unit will soon head to Hong Kong and Thailand for further schedules of shoot.

Kabali, directed by Young filmmaker PA Ranjith and produced by Kalaipuli S Thanu stars Radhika Apte, Dhansika, Dinesh and Kalaiarasan as other leads. Santhosh Naraynan is the music composer.

items.title: Akhil Akkineni Akhil Film censor report
items.content:
Akkineni's clan Akhil Akkineni lead actor debut film Akhil has wrapped up its censor formalities with U/A certification from regional censor board.

Akhil film has finished its censor
with out single cut and censor board members appreciated the makers for producing such film. Sayeesha Saighal is romancing Akhil in this commercial mass action entertainer. Akhil trailers and songs are well received by the audience in a positive way.

VV Vinayak directorial Akhil is now all set to be released on November 11th on the eve of Diwali festive season. Anup Rubens and SS Thaman are the music composers for the film while Nithin is producing it. Brahmanandam, Vennela Kishore, Mukesh Rishi and others are playing crucial characters in this movie.

items.title: Rudhramadevi Movie 1 Million Collections in US
items.content:
Anushka's Rudhramadevi film which has been released recently is doing well at box office with rave reviews and good word of mouth all over.

Zustcinema here brings latest update is
that Rudhramadevi has collected 1 Million collections in US and running successfully in good number of screens in Overseas. Rudhramadevi has completed its 25 days and heading towards 50 Days soon. items.title: Jr.NTR dual role act in Nannaku Prematho !
items.content:
Young Tiger NTR is quite since couple of months with the non-stop shoot schedules of Nannaku Prematho has taken a short break for its last schedule. Meanwhile buzz is that Jr.NTR will be seen in dual roles in this film.

Tinsel Town sources reveals
that NTR will be sporting two different characters in this revenge backdrop entertainer. The Temper actor will be seen as a cop and other as an pshyco in Nannaku Prematho. However their is no official update regarding this. Filmmakers are planning to begin final schedule of the movie in Spain post Diwali.

Jr.NTR is romancing Rakul Preet Singh in this commercial entertainer which also features Jagapathi Babu and Rajendra Prasad in important roles. Sukumar is the director and Devi Sri Prasad is scoring tunes for this 2016 Sankranthi release.

items.title: Mahesh Babu, Salman Khan in AR Murugadoss direction !
items.content:
South Indian filmmaker AR Murugadoss, who is currently busy with the woman-centric film Akira with Sonakshi Sinha as lead has finalized his next two films, if the buzz is to be believed. Murugadoss has already wrapped entire shoot except for one song.

AR Murugadoss has already
finalized a film with Tamil-Telugu bilingual movie with Super Star Mahesh Babu as lead. The shooting schedules will commence in 2016, and the movie is also likely to hit the screens in the same year.
Now, the latest we hear is Murugadoss is likely to direct Salman Khan for a new film. Sources revealed that “Murugadoss has narrated a script to Salman Khan and the latter liked it. The duo working on the dates and the film will be finalized.”

Though there have been reports earlier that Murugadoss may direct Vijay in 2016, looks like we need to wait for few more months for it to happen.

items.title: Naga Shaurya, Niharika Konidela film from Nov 16
items.content:
Niharika Konidela is set to make her big-screen debut as lead lady opposite Naga Shaurya, and the film’s regular shooting schedules will commence from November 16.

The untitled film is said to be a
romantic entertainer, and it will take shape in the hands of director Mallela Theeramlo Sirimalle Chettu. Madhura Sreedhar along with news channel TV9 will jointly produce the movie. A.Abhinay and Krishna Bhatta are the co-producers. The pre-production works have come to end, and the shooting schedules will be shot at a brisk pace.

Naga Shaurya has completed the shooting schedules for a couple of films Kalyana Vaibhogame in Nandini Reddy direction and Abbayitho Ammayi in Veera fame Ramesh Varma direction. The release dates of both the films are to be announced.

items.title: Naga Chaitanya, Nithiin teams up for Majnu
items.content:
Naga Chaitanya’s new film Majnu is getting bigger day after day. We have informed earlier that Venkatesh and Nagarjuna are being considered for the cameo roles in the film. Now, the latest buzz is young hero Nithiin being approached for yet another crucial cameo.

Apparently Nithiin has given his nod for
a cameo, and he will be seen essaying the role of Arivazhagan in the original version. Anupama Parameshwaran and Shruti Haasan are roped in as the lead ladies and the film casts three heroines. However, an official announcement on the Majnu cast and crew is awaited.

Majnu is slated for a grand scale launch on November 30, and the regular shoot will be canned from first week of December in the locales of Visakhapatnam, Rajahmundry, Europe, Araku Valley, Pollachi, Goa. Majnu, a romantic drama will release in March 2016.

Naga Chaitanya’s Saahasam Swasaga Saagipo in Gautham Menon direction is gearing up for a release soon.

items.title: Tamanna shakes leg with Bellamkonda Srinivas again

Milky White Beauty Tamanna has sizzled alongside Bellamkonda Srinivas in his debut movie Alludu Seenu in VV Vinayak directorial, and the special song has got quite a good response.

items.title: IIFA UTSAVAM 2015 kick off with a Premiere Voting Event
items.content:
THE INTERNATIONAL INDIAN FILM ACADEMY (IIFA) ANNOUNCES THE FIRST-EVER‘IIFA UTSAVAM’: A MAGNIFICIENT CELEBRATION OF THE CINEMA OF SOUTH INDIA

South Indian Cinema Stars Prakash Raj, Rana and Venkatesh among the first to cast their vote

Hyderabad, November 3rd, 2015: December 2015 will witness IIFA celebrations, India’s biggest Cinema event, celebrating South Indian Cinema like never before. Marking a landmark event in the illustrious history of the Cinema of South India, The International Indian Film Academy (IIFA) has announced Fortune Sunflower Oil IIFA UTSAVAM co-powered by Gionee smartphone- a magnificent extravaganza envisioned to honor and recognize the best of South India’s film industry.

Spanning across three days, IIFA Utsavam will debut on the 4th, 5th & 6th of December, 2015 at Gachibowli Outdoor Stadium, Hyderabad. The broadcast partner for the extravaganza is the Sun Network, while the Title sponsor is Fortune Sunflower Oil from the Adani Group.

South Indian Cinema film stars showed their support by voting for their favourite movies and talent at the IIFA Utsavam Voting Day and announcement event held at Park Hyatt, Hyderabad. Among the biggest names of South Indian cinema Prakash Raj, Rana and Venkatesh were among the first to cast their vote.

Bringing together the biggest megastars from the South Indian Film Industry including Kamal Hassan, A.R Rahman, Trisha, Venkatesh, Chiranjeevi, Mahesh Babu, Nagarjuna, Mohanlal, Kavya, Madhavan, Priyadarshan, Shivrajkumar, Puneet Rajkumar, among other superstars will all congregate for one grand Utsavam- the IIFA Utsavam.

Encompassing four massive film industries of South India, the Tamil, the Telugu, the Malayalam and the Kannada - The Cinema of South India is being celebrated as a single entity. Known for its larger-than-life movies, flamboyant superstars, immense talent pool, technologically advanced productions, loyal fan following, the Cinema of the South has created waves not only in India but also made a name for itself on the global map.

IIFA Utsavam’s illustrious Advisory Board comprises eminent personalities include A R Rahman, Kamal Hassan, Suresh Babu, KS Rama Rao, Boney Kapoor, Nagarjuna, Allu Aravind, Resul Pookutty, R B Choudhary, Ram Kumar, Mukesh, Sibi Malayil, B Unnikrishnan, Ramesh Aravind and Radikaa Sharathkumar.

A.R Rahman commented “Truly IIFA Utsavam is going to be a huge event for the Indian Film Industry and the entire fraternity is looking forward to it. With the attention it is going to receive, I am sure it will change the way how South Indian cinema is perceived not only in India but world over. I am very excited to extend my support IIFA Utsavam.”

Kamal Haasan said “IIFA Utsavam is a wonderful initiative taken by the International Indian Film Academy to help build the outreach of film industries across India. Given the global acclaim of the IIFA platform I am confident that it will become an instant opportunity for greater recognition to South Indian film industries and our work. It is great to see an endeavour such as IIFA Utsavam to help give our cinema maximum exposure to audiences and media around the world. Having participated at previous IIFA Weekends, it is a truly impressive and world class brand to be associated with. So I am excited and look forward to the prospects of bringing IIFA to India with IIFA Utsavam and the anticipated scale, glamour and presentation that they will be creating in India at the event in Hyderabad.

Suresh Babu said “IIFA Utsavam marks the beginning of an incredible journey where the diversity of South Indian Cinema can come alive onto one common stage. December will hold a very special occasion for us as the very first edition of IFA Utsavam unfolds.”

Day 1 of the event will see IIFA partnering with FICCI for the FICCI-IIFA Business Forum. The forum will feature prominent film personalities, CEOs, policy makers and industry leaders meet to discuss Cinema-tourism, infrastructure, media, cinema co-productions and investment opportunities.

On Day 2, IIFA Utsavam will felicitate and celebrate talent from Tamil & Malayalam film industries.

On the final day, IIFA Utsavam will felicitate and celebrate the best talent from Kannada and Telugu cinema. Nominees be vying for 12 popular awards; 6 special awards will be presented to winners from each region. Common across the 4 language-cinemas, technical Awards will be presented for 10 categories.

items.title: Trisha Launches NAC Jewellers at Kanchipuram
items.content:
Kanchipuram, 2nd November, 2015: India’s trusted jewellery brand, NAC Jewellers, today made a grand foray into Kanchipuram with its first exclusive outlet at Kamarajar Salai. Brand Ambassador, actress Ms. Trisha Krishnan, inaugurated the outlet of NAC Jewellers as the chief guest along with Mr. N. Anantha Padmanabhan, Managing director, NAC Jewellers Pvt. Ltd and Mr. N. Anandha Ramanujam, Director, NAC Jewellers Pvt Ltd.

Spread across 10,000 sq.ft,
the store will house a variety of jewellery line up and has exclusively dedicated sections for Diamond, Gold, Platinum and Antique jewellery catering to every occasion.

Started in the year 1973, NAC Jewellers is one of the premium jewellery brands based in Tamil Nadu catering to customers worldwide. NAC Jewellers, with a wide range of contemporary collections, is renowned for its rich history, immense customer trust and loyalty and a perfect abode of supremely crafted Diamond, Gold, Platinum, Ruby, Emerald and Silver Jewellery.

Commenting on the occasion, Mr. Anantha Padmanabhan, Managing Director, NAC Jewellers Pvt Ltd, said, “It gives me great honour to expand our brand to the temple town of Tamil Nadu. Over the years, NAC has evolved into a destination that offers innovative and vibrant jewellery collections for different generations. Our expansive jewellery line up, top-notch infrastructure coupled with impeccable services is a commitment towards fulfilling the expectations of our customers.”

Inaugurating the store, brand ambassador, actress Ms. Trisha Krishnan, said, “I am very delighted to launch the first exclusive showroom of NAC Jewellers in Kanchipuram. The store is indeed a stunning landmark for the temple town and the extensive collection is an absolute treat for the jewellery lovers. This is one among the many memorable days of my association with NAC Jewellers and I’m thoroughly enjoying the journey so far.”

As part of the store launch and festive season, NAC Jewellers will offer a discount of Rs.500 per sovereign for gold jewellery purchase and Rs.500 off per Karat for Diamond jewellery.

items.title: Kalyan Ram Sher Movie Review
items.content:
Nandamuri Kalyanram who has scored a good hit this year with Pataas is back to big-screens again with Sher this Friday. Kalyanram’s longtime associate Malli directed the film and Sonal Chauhan paired up with him. Will Kalyan Ram manage to deliver yet another hit? Read Sher Movie Review on Zust Cinema for more details.

Story
Gautham (Kalyan Ram) is a BTech graduate and he helps his father (Rao Ramesh) in his business. He is quite helpful and comes to rescue to anyone in danger, and goes to any extent for his family. He falls in love with Nandini (Sonal Chauhan) which leads him to lock horns with local don Puppy (Vikramjeet Virk). Gautham enters agreement with Nandini’s father, a Police Commissioner (Sayaji Shinde) who only wants to become a DGP by any means. Puppy makes deal with Nandini’s father to make him a DGP if the latter agrees Nandini’s father with him. What does Gautham do now and how will he solve the issue is the rest.

Performances

Kalyan Ram performs well, rather in a weak characterization. He seems to be the director’s actor and you can see his commitment for the movie. He is good in action scenes while okay in the dances.

Sonal Chauhan looks pretty and good, but she fails to emote. Her glamour quotient in the songs may please the masses.

Vikramjeet is convincing. Mukesh Rushi and Shayaji Shinde are routine and nothing much to offer, Brahmanandam does the same regular role while Posani’s role is poorly etched. Prabhas Seenu has nothing much role while Duvvasi Mohan is better to an extent. Thagubothu Ramesh is wasted and Fish Venkat manages to evoke some laughs. Other filled the screens.

Technical Analysis

Thaman’s musical scores are mediocre and so is the BGM. Cinematography is pretty ordinary and neither the songs have the apt placement. Direction is bad; Story is routine while the screenplay fails to impress. Editing is consistent with a run times of 118 minutes. Dialogues are apt and neat. Production values are standard.

Analysis

Sher storyline is intriguing, and the characterizations are well-etched, but the execution has totally faltered. The screenplay fails to interest you, none of the proceedings keep you glued to the screens.
Only few dialogues and some entertaining scenes in the first hour are likeable. But that is insufficient for the narration of the story. Scenes elevating villain are very weak and thus the hero elevation gets never interesting, and as a result the entire revenge plot is never emotionally-connective.

Sher first hour is a bit entertaining with some comedy and breezy moments here and there, but the second hour is very weak leaving you to boredom. The proceedings only highlight several loopholes with cliched screenplay and characterizations. All in all, Sher offers nothing new to Tollywood audiences.

ZC Take

Sher- What a Bore!!!

Zustcinema Sher Movie Rating :-  2.25 / 5

items.title: Rajugari Gadhi Movie Review
items.content:
TV Reality show Director Ohmkar's second Telugu Feature Film Rajugari Gadhi has been released worldwide with much expectations. Omhkar's brother Aswin is debuting as lead actor with this horror genre thriller. Zustcinema presents Raju Gari Gadhi Movie Review.

Story :- 
The story opens in a dreaded haunted bungalow in the village called Nandigama and who ever wanted to find the mystery were not seen again which was said that the spirit has ended their life. However a renowned Telivision Team wanted to raise their TRP's and goes on searching for an interesting topic where they finally comes to known about the bungalow in Nandigama.

TV Network selects a group of Youngsters to live in Raju Gari Mahal for a week period and who comes in alive could win an amount of 3 Crores. The youngsters goes to the mahal and rest of the story of what happens to them forms crux...

Performances :-

Shakalaka Shankar along with Dhanraj carried out the entire film on their shoulders. The entire credit of the film should be given to them. They are humorous in their well itched characters.

Ashwin, brother of Omhkar is just ok and does his part to his conscience for the debutante of his in Tollywood.

Dhanya Balakrishna is good, Chetan Cheenu does a clean performance. Poorna is sticked to her role so to be Vidyu Lekha Raman. Sapthagiri is waster and Others does their part well.

Technical Analysis :- 

Sai Karthik tunes are ok while his background score has elevated the scenes to the core. Sahi Suresh's art work is impressive. The mahal set was showcased well and cinematography should be commendable. Ohmkar has succeeded in presenting the entertaining first half and suspense thriller in the second half. Productions Values are good.

Analysis :- 

First half of Raju Gari Gadhi brings up the hilarious comedy and the key notes of thrilling aspects which are in the way.. In this half, Shakalaka Shankar, Dhanraj, Chetan Cheenu does their best along with Ashwin. Few entertaining scenes between Shankar and Dhanraj are superb. The interval scenes leaves the audience to wait in the second half. 

Second half opens up with serious suspense elements in Raju Gari Mahal and slowly the twists goes on revealing. But few aspects in this half misses the logic and scenes are deviated which makes boredom. The climax has been well-showcased but the twists are revealed in a simple way.

ZC Take :- Raju Gari Gadhi is an hilarious, suspense thriller


Zustcinema Raju Gari Gadhi Review :-  2.75 / 5

items.title: Kanche Movie Review
items.content:
Varun Tej, Pragya Jaiswal have teamed up for Kanche, in the direction of unique filmmaker Krish. Kanche is the first Indian movie set on World War II, and the producers have spent huge budget on the technicalities. Will Kanche manage to impress Tollywood audiences. Read Kanche Movie Review on ZustCinema.com

Story
Kanche story is set in 1930’s backdrop. Dhoopati Hari Babu (Varun Tej) is a lower-middle class young student who hopes to reach higher position. Hari Babu couldn’t bear the flaws in the society, where few people build some fences for their own benefits. He gets to know a lady from a rich family in his same village, and the duo fall in love. However, their love draws flak some village heads due to the society set rules. What does Hari Babu do now? Why does he become a soldier? What happens to their love story is the crux of Kanche.

Performances

Varun Tej has done justice to this performance-oriented role. His role is quite emotional one and Varun Tej is impressive in articulating right expressions dialogue-delivery, while he is attractive love and action scenes too.

Pragya Jaiswal is classy and impresses with her performance, though she haven’t had much of the scope, except for three to four vital portions. She shares good chemistry with Varun tej in the songs.

Nikethan Dheer is apt and perfect and delivered his best. He would sure bag some Telugu films in his kitty after Kanche. Srinivas Avasarala provides comic relief and plays significant part while Gollapudi Maruthi Rao and Singeetham Srinivas adds their experience to their key roles. Others are adequate.

Technical Analysis

The technical values are rich. Cinematography is on top notch, Soundtrack is impressive and all the songs are brilliantly shot. Art work is amazing while the Sai Madhav Burra’s dialogues standout. Director Krish follows his unique way in narrating Kanche story too. The story is unique and the writing is clever. Krish shows his direction prowess in several scenes, while the screenplay in second hour is a bit slow. Editing is okay. Production values are rich.

Analysis

Director Krish is known for emotional content-driven films, and Kanche is no different, where he tries to narrate the story of a young lower middle class guy who hopes to fight against the flaws in the society. Kudos to director Krish who has strictly stuck to his storyline and strong content rather than opting for unnecessary commercial elements, masala or action or songs.

The entire proceedings go according to the story, the comedy is situational, the war scenes are intense and the climax is emotional. The run-time is the major asset besides the unique story and brilliant dialogues.

While the first half is excellent in setting the story and with racy screenplay, the second half however is a bit slow-paced, though the climax is the biggest asset with lots of emotional-packed content.

ZC Take

Kanche- Honest & brave attempt by Krish!

Zustcinema Kanche Rating :- 3 / 5

items.title: Ram Charan Bruce Lee Movie Review
items.content:
Ram Charan’s Bruce Lee has hit the big-screens today on a massive scale. Ram Charan Bruce Lee Movie Review below on Zustcinema. It has turned most anticipated films of the season not just for being Ram Charan and Srinu Vytla combo, but also for Mega Star Chiranjeevi’s cameo. Let’s see what we have in store for us with Bruce Lee The Fighter Movie Review.

Story
Karthik (Ram Charan) loves his family to the core and sacrifices anything for them. He gives up his education for his sister Kavya(Kriti Kharbhanda) sake, and ends up being a stuntman with screen name Bruce Lee. Riya (Rakul Preet) is a game developer who falls for Karthik assuming he is a cop, and plans to design a game on him. As the story progresses, Karthik’s family starts facing problems from Jayraj (Sampath) and his son Deepak Raj (Arun Vijay). Who is this Jayraj and Deepak Raj and why did they mess with Karthik and his family? How does Karthik solve the problems? Where does Chiranjeevi come in? forms the rest.

Performances

Ram Charan looked super stylish and carries the film on his shoulders. His dances and fights are major highlight as always, while he also does a good job in the emotional scenes with Kriti Karbanda and Rao Ramesh.

Mega Star Chiranjeevi’s cameo is another major highlight, and it’s a delight to watch Chiranjeevi back on big-screens. He proves yet again that he has terrific screen presence. All credit to Srinu Vytla for showing him in a very good cameo.

Rakul Preet Singh is glamorous and gorgeous and fits in the Riya role aptly. Her role does have a bit of humor touch, and she does her dances on par with Ram Charan.

Kriti Kharbanda is beautiful and enacted well, while Arun Vijay earns brownie points for his balancing act. Brhamanandam is wasted in poor role, while Jaya Prakash Reddy manages to evoke some laughter. Rao Ramesh is perfect, Nadiya has not much to do, while Sampath Raj, Tisca Chopra are good. Vennela Kishore, . Posani Krishna Murali and Prithvi played their brief portions.

Technical Analysis

Thaman’s musical scores are very impressive, and Ram Charan, Rakul and the choreographers’ team have justified with the amazing dances for all the songs. Manoj Paramahamsa’s camera work is on top notch. Sreenu Vaitla’s direction was decent in the first hour, while the narration is slightly weak in the second hour. Story is predictable and screenplay lacked Sreenu Vaitla’s mark style. Dialogues are neat and entertaining while editing could have been better in the second half. Production values are rich.

Analysis

Srinu Vytla who is known to make entertaining films packing with loads of comedy and commercial elements, has this time focused more on action and emotional drama with Bruce Lee. The first half of the film is pretty good with a decent story setup and neat lead characterizations. But the second hour has turns quite routine and the tempo drops drastically. Sadly, the comedy doesn’t work in this Sreenu Vaitla movie, and too many comedians come and go.

However, Ram Charan is great in his dances, fights and improves in his emotional scenes. Besides Ram Charan, Chiranjeevi’s special appearance, Thaman’s trendy tunes and songs choreography, Rakul Preet Singh and JP comedy to an extent are positive points. On the negative side, lack of entertaining scenes in second hour and routine screenplay played the spoilsport.

All in all, Bruce Lee makes a decent family entertainer, if you don’t mind the routine stuff you have already watched in many Telugu films earlier.

ZC Take

Bruce Lee The Fighter- A regular family entertainer!

Zustcinema Bruce Lee Rating :-  3 / 5

items.title: Rudramadevi Movie Review - Rudramadevi Critic Rating
items.content:
Rudramadevi Review first on Net . Anushka, Gunasekhar’s Visual Extravaganza Rudramadevi Movie Review exclusively on Zustcinema. This historical stereoscopic 3D film features Allu Arjun, Rana, Catherine, Nithya Menon, Krishnam Raju, Prakash Raj in central roles. Read the Rudramadevi Review below..

Story
Italian merchant traveller Marco polo (Gary Tantony) shares his views of Kakatiya kingdom in Orugallu ruled by Ganapathi Devudu (Krishnam Raju) and his daughter Rudramadevi (Anushka) who was raised as male child Rudradevudu to safeguard the Kakatiya Kingdom rule as its successor, due to the threatening invasions from neighboring rivals. Prince Maha Deva (Vikramjeet Virk), a Yadava King from Nidadavolu, and their cousins Hari Hara Devudu (Suman), Murari Devudu (Adithya Menon) were the arch rivals of Kakatiya dynasty, who waits for the right time to invade a war to capture the Kakatiya Empire. Rudradeva alias Rudramadevi has to work on her mission to safeguard Kakatiya dynasty from the rivals and how Gona Ganna Reddy and Chalukya Veera Bhadra joined her in war is the rest.

Performances

Anushka looked royal, majestic, and the warrior queen roles seem to be tailor-made for the actress. She gets into the skin of Rudramadevi role showcasing the male and female traits simultaneously in her act, with varied emotions.

Allu Arjun in the role of Gona Ganna Reddy delivers stellar performance. He has terrific screen presence and impresses with his powerful dialogue delivery with his dialect, body language and attitude.

Rana as Chalukya Veerabhadra does his act well, but his characterization hasn’t had much scope, Nithya Menon plays yet another crucial role as princess, though is limited to four-five scenes.

Prakash Raj is perfect as Rudrama Devi’s guru Shivadevayya, who has some crucial scenes in second hour. Krishnam Raju is justifying in Ganapathi Devudu role, Suman, Aditya Menon, Baba Sehgal were limited but played significant roles.

Technical Analysis

Ilayaraja’s musical scores aren’t pleasing and the background score could be more elevating in the crucial war scenes and significant episodes. Cinematography is not grand enough for such historical movie. Such historical 3D films need grand technical values especially VFX works, but the graphics works are bad. Dialogues were apt, Art work by Thota Tharani is grand and the sets are lavishly designed. Neeta Lulla’s costumes were regal. Srikar Prasad’s editing could have been crisp. Production values of Guna team Works are ok.

Analysis

Rudramadevi is made based on the real history of warrior queen, who ruled Kakatiya Dynasty. Gunassekhar has made the film with a blend of history and some fiction. Though the director showed off some of the facts, the basic story isn’t made gripping, the screenplay lacked transparency. The casting is perfect but the characterizations are limited and are neither gripping. The only characterization which standout entirely in the movie is the Gona Ganna Reddy and Allu Arjun is the show stealer of the film. But the remaining characterization including the main Rudramadevi role lacked conviction, though Anushka tried to save with her screen presence.

Such historical subjects need gripping narration and visuals need to be grandeur, but the CG work is not up to the mark in this 80 Crore budget movie. While the first half moves on a smooth ride with a couple of twists, the second half is inconsistent, lacked clarity, while the climax is weak.

Gunasekhar has put in lots of effort and money on Rudramadevi, and his sincere attempt to make a film on untold history is noticeable in several episodes, but the film had some major drawbacks with weak screenplay, Rudramadevi characterization blend, unimpressive stunts and worst VFX works.

ZC Take :-

Rudramadevi- Gona Ganna Reddy is the saving grace!

Zustcinema Rudramadevi Rating :-  3 / 5

items.title: Anushka’s Rudhramadevi pre-release buzz
items.content:
With Anushka in the main role, the historical movie Rudramadevi is all set for a grand scale release on 9th October. This first historical stereoscopic 3D movie in India is directed and produced by Gunasekhar on a massive scale under his production house Guna Team Works banner.

Besides Anushka, the film has
very impressive casting including Allu Arjun who will be seen in the Warrior role as Gona Ganna Reddy. His role is going to be the major highlight with 50 minutes screentime. Rana will be seen as Chalukya Veerabhadra in this historical movie, while Rebel Star Krishnam Raju will be seen as Ganapathi Deva Chakravarthi, Prakash Raj as Mahamanthri Sivadevayya, Ajay as Prasadaditya, Baba Sehgal as Naga devudu, JayaPrakash Reddy as Amba Devudu, Catherine Tresa as Annambika and Hamsanandini as Madanika.

Apart from the huge casting, Rudramadevi which is shot in 3D format has massive sets, exotic locales, expensive jewellery and royal costumes. Padma Shri Thota Tharani supervised the sets, Neetha Lulla worked as costume designer, Ajay Vincent cranked the camera, Ram -Laxman supervised the stunts and Maestro Ilayaraja provided the soundtrack.
Rudramadevi has been under production from two years, and the historical film based on reality happened around 800 years back. The whopping budget, the historical story, the VFX works, the 3D format and the casting are all raising the expectations on Rudramadevi.

Gunasekhar says he believed in the story of Rudramadevi to take such massive risks? Will his risks and hard work he had put in pay off? Keep watching this space for Rudramadevi movie review…

items.title: Gopichand, Regina pairs up for Soukyam
items.content:
Actor Gopichand is now working with Ravi Kumar Chowdary for a new film which is currently busy with its hectic shoot schedules at full swing.

Zustcinema here exclusively
updates that Gopichand's new movie has been now titled as Soukyam. It is now clear that Gopichand is following the sentiment like title Lakshyam, Shouryam and Loukyam films. This movie is touted to be an action comedy.

Soukyam features Regina Cassandra as lady love of Gopichand while tunes are being rendered by Anup Rubens and cinematography is by Prasad Murrela. Bhavya Creations is producing Soukyam film.

Soukyam is scheduled for a grand release on 25th December.

items.title: Pawan Kalyan extensively shooting for Sardar Gabbarsingh
items.content:
Powerstar Pawan Kalyan starrer latest film Sardar Gabbarsingh is busy with its non-stop shoot schedule happening in Hyderabad.

In the last week filmmakers
wrapped up an item song and few crucial scenes on Pawan Kalyan, Raai Laxmi and other artists. Currently police station scenes are being shot. Pawan Kalyan is looking serious to wrap up the shoot as per the schedule date.

Sardar Gabbar Singh film features Kajal Agarwal as Pawan Kalyan's love interest in this commercial mass entertainer. Bobby is the director while tunes are by Devi Sri Prasad and cinematography is by Arthur Wilson. Northstar Entertainments, Pawan Kalyan Creative Works in association with Eros International are producing the film.

items.title: Sai Dharam Tej, Rashi Khanna's roles in Supreme
items.content:
Sai Dharam Tej playing the title role in the upcoming film titled Supreme, which has commenced its first schedule of shoot in Ramoji Film City from October 7th.

Supreme is touted to be a
commercial action comedy entertainer. In the first schedule romantic and few comedy scenes are planned to be shot on the main lead characters. Rashi Khanna is romancing Sai Dharam Tej for the first time in Supreme film. Filmmakers informed that Sai Dharam Tej is essaying the role of a cab driver while Rashi Khanna as a touch cop role in Supreme.

Posani Krishna Murali, Sai Kumar, Kabir Singh, Jayaprakash Reddy, Srinivas Reddy are playing prominent roles. Patas shot fame Director Anil Ravipudi is wielding the megaphone for this film while musical scores are by Sai Prakash and DOP is by Sai Sreeram. Dil Raju is producing Supreme film under Sri Venkateswara Creations banner.
